    description:
      "\u003cp\u003eAt the City of Plano, our values make us who we are and guide us as we SERVE our city.  As members of Team Plano, our organizational Values (what is most important to us) make up the acronym, SERVE (Stewardship Engaged Respectful Visionary Excellence). \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSummary of Duties:  Under general supervision, works with business partners within one or more business processes to align technology solutions with business strategies. Supports one or more moderately complex business processes; serves as a team member.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEXAMPLES OF ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eManagement reserves the rights to add, modify, change, or rescind the work assignments of different positions and to make reasonable accommodations so that qualified employees can perform the essential functions of the job.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEstablishes and maintains liaison relationships with business partners and TS to provide effective technical solutions; seeks opportunities to improve business relationships.\nCreates and maintains system models, specifications, diagrams, and charts to provide direction to teams.\nDevelops user test cases and validates test results during testing; executes test cases and test units; may validate application functionality after OS level updates.\nInvestigates, resolves, and escalates problems; may recommend solutions and identify need for technical assistance to aid in problem resolution; informs clients of problems, issues, and resolutions; ensures IT solutions meet client needs.\nProvides assistance in determining the need for a change requests; may implement changes.\nKeeps clients informed of problems, issues, and resolutions.\nCoaches and transfers knowledge to less experienced team members.\nParticipates in, and may lead peer programing sessions; participates in established code review processes and procedures; initiates team code review as needed.\nConducts research on hardware and software products to justify recommendation and support purchasing efforts.\nPerform best coding practices with comments, naming conventions, code structure, and mitigating security risks.\nCompetent in programming and debugging across multiple modules and dealing with related external dependencies.\nMay research and implement new and emerging languages, frameworks, and technologies for solutions when appropriate.\nConducts end user training; writes well defined end user documentation including but not limited to solution user manuals; may review or establish end user training curriculum and end user documentation for completeness.\nProvides system and application administration and support to multiple platforms used to develop solutions in accordance with operational management guidelines.\nWrites code that consumes one or more API end points; authors API end points for multiple applications; may engineer one or more applications and services.\nFields incoming issues and problem tickets from end-users to resolve application and software issues within servers, databases, and other mission critical application systems.\nRecords, tracks, and documents problem solving processes through resolution.\nAssists in maintaining and enhancing performance of all new and existing software and applications across the organization; tests fixes and performs post-resolution follow-ups to ensure problems have been adequately resolved.\nPosts software updates, drivers, knowledge bases and frequently asked question resources on company intranet to assist in problem resolution.\nPerforms preventative maintenance including the installation of service packs, patches, hot fixes, anti-virus, and related software.\nPerforms other duties as assigned.\nWorks with business partners within one or more business processes to align technology solutions with business strategies.\nRegular and consistent attendance for the assigned work schedule is essential. \nMarginal Duties:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePerforms other duties as assigned.\nTypical Decisions:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eResponds to problem statements and questions from internal and external business partners by developing custom applications, websites, and mobile apps. Determines technical needs of end-users and provides appropriate guidance.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMinimum Qualifications:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eKnowledge of: Agile/Scrum Methodology; Design principles and best practices regarding UX/UI; Mobile app development in iOS (Swift), Android (JAVA), or utilizing a cross-platform solution such as Xamarin, PhoneGap or React Native.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSkill in: Communicating effectively both verbally and in writing; programming and debugging across multiple modules and dealing with related external dependencies.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eProgramming languages, frameworks, and technologies used in the environment such as HTML, JavaScript, CSS, NodeJS, C#, Python, AngularJS, Aurelia, SQL, PHP, AWS Aurora, AWS Lambda, AWS CodePipline, and others. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEducation: Bachelor’s degree in computer science or related field; or four years of related experience.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExperience: Six (6) years of experience as an Application Integrator/Developer or related field.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAny work-related experience resulting in acceptable proficiency levels in the above Minimum Qualifications is an acceptable substitute for the above specified education and experience requirements\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLicenses and Certifications: Texas Class C driver’s license may be required.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAWS Certified Developer Associate\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCompTIA Security+ or MTA Security and\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAny one of the following:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCompTIA Network+\nCompTIA Server+\nMTA Networking\nMTA Server\nEither one of the following:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMCSA Web Applications\nMCSA Universal Windows Platform\nConditions of Employment:   Must pass a drug test, driver’s license check if license required, criminal history background check, periodic CJIS background check (for positions requiring access into Police buildings) and social security number verification check.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePhysical Demands and Working Conditions:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is primarily an office classification although standing in work areas and walking between work areas may be required. Finger dexterity is needed to access, enter, and retrieve data using a computer keyboard or calculator and to operate standard office equipment; vision to read printed materials and a computer screen; hearing and speech to communicate in person and over the telephone. Positions in this classification occasionally bend, stoop, kneel, reach, push, and pull drawers open and closed to retrieve and file information. Employees must possess the ability to lift, carry, push, and pull materials and objects weighing up to 25 pounds.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEmployees work in an office environment with moderate noise levels, controlled temperature conditions, and no direct exposure to hazardous physical substances. Employees may interact with upset staff and/or public and private representatives in interpreting and enforcing departmental policies and procedures.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe above statements are intended to describe the general nature and level of work being performed and are not intended to be an exhaustive list of all responsibilities, duties and skills which may be required. The position also requires meeting the essential requirements of the Physical Demands and Working Conditions, with or without reasonable accommodation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEqual Opportunity Employer - EOE/M/F/V/D\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOpen positions are subject to close without notice.\u003c/p\u003e\n",
