    company_url: "https://corp.sertifi.com/",
    location: "Chicago",
    title: "Senior Software Developer",
    description:
      "\u003cp\u003eSertifi offers an Agreement Platform built for businesses who need a more efficient and secure way to manage the full contract process. We simplify how businesses send and collect agreements and payments by bringing it all into one secure platform. Sertifi automates business processes, saves you time from performing repetitive tasks, enhances security and PCI-compliance, and provides customers an easy and convenient way to do business with your company. Thousands of businesses around the world use Sertifi to streamline their contracts and payment processes, recognize revenue faster, and increase job efficiency.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe are looking for a talented and highly motivated Full Stack Developer to help launch new features and expand capabilities of our electronic signature and payment application. The web application is written in ASP.NET, with client-side Angular/Typescript, Node.JS, JavaScript, and jQuery. The back-end database is SQL Server with web services used to expose a rich and simple to use API.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOur ideal candidate is a self-starter who is capable of building advanced ASP.NET applications as part of a team. You must be able to fully understand the ins and outs of ASP.NET, how it works, or be able to pick up a book or online tutorial and teach yourself when something unknown comes your way. You’ll have the opportunity to immediately contribute and see results of your work in use by millions of users across the globe. This position reports to our Engineering Manager in our downtown Chicago office.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eChallenges You’ll Tackle:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTake ownership of, architect, build and scale business critical services\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDevelop a deep understanding of the relevant business areas and various components in the stack\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDevelop integration strategies\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat You’ll Need to Succeed:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e5+ years of experience working on large scale web applications\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExpert in .NET based technologies and ecosystem - .NET Framework through 4.5, WebAPI, ASP.NET MVC\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor the Front End we’re looking for expert level knowledge of Angular/Typescript and Node.JS\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWorking knowledge of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWeb service consumption and design experience (REST or SOAP)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSolid competencies in data structures, design patterns, algorithms\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eStrong web application design and architectural skills\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUnderstanding of data layer concerns and working knowledge of SQL\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBachelor’s degree in Computer Science or equivalent experience\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNice to haves:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExperience with mercurial or git\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExperience with cloud platforms such as Azure and Salesforce\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExperience with SSO flows and SAML\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExperience with eCommerce payments or PDF parsing and manipulation\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExperience with message bus/distributed systems\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat’s in it for you:\u003c/strong\u003e You will work in a collaborative office environment that welcomes new ideas and allows you to make an immediate impact on the team. You can also expect to have dedicated heads down time to code along with time set aside each month to work on Innovation ideas. Additionally, we offer great benefits such as: competitive salary, medical/dental/vision insurance, short-term and long-term disability insurance, 401k with company match, paid parental leave, life insurance, pre-tax Transit Benefit Program, casual work environment, weekly team lunches, company outings, and a convenient River North location close to public transit.\u003c/p\u003e\n",
